+This post explains what data recovery actually costs, why prices vary, and how ZA Support approaches recovery in our Johannesburg location.
+
+## How Data Recovery Pricing Works
+
+Data recovery isn't a fixed cost because each device fails differently. A MacBook with a failed hard drive requires different work than an iMac with corrupted system files, which is different again from an iPhone with water damage affecting the storage controller.
+
+We start every recovery case with a diagnostic assessment, R599 (including VAT). This is not a guessing game. Our technicians physically inspect the device, run diagnostics on the storage hardware, and determine whether the data is recoverable, partially recoverable, or lost permanently. That assessment tells us the real cost.
+
+From there, pricing depends on three factors: the type of device, the cause of failure, and the extent of damage. A straightforward SSD recovery on a MacBook Air costs less than recovering data from a failed hard drive with mechanical damage. Water damage affecting the logic board alongside storage corruption costs more because we're often repairing the logic board first, work like this requires specialised soldering and component-level repair, which falls under our [logic board repair](/logic-board-repair) services.
+
+We've recovered data from over 18,000 Apple devices in the past five years. That experience means we can quote accurately and rarely encounter surprises during recovery.
+
+## Typical Data Recovery Costs in Johannesburg
+
+For most devices, expect the following ranges:
+
+**MacBook and Mac mini:** R2,800-R8,500 (SSD or hard drive recovery)
+**iMac:** R3,200-R9,200 (larger drives, sometimes mechanical damage)
+**iPad and iPhone:** R1,800-R4,500 (storage controller damage is common with water exposure)
+**External drives:** R1,200-R6,800 (depends on interface and damage type)
+
+These figures include the assessment. If we determine data is unrecoverable before we begin extraction, you pay only the R599 assessment fee. We don't charge for work we haven't done.
+
+Load shedding has created a specific problem: unscheduled power cuts corrupting file systems. We see this at least four times weekly. These cases are typically cheaper to recover because the storage hardware is intact, only the file system needs repair. Cost: usually R1,800-R3,500.
+
+## Why Turnaround Varies
+
+Recovery speed depends on hardware complexity and data volume. A corrupted SSD on a MacBook Air takes 2-4 working days. A mechanical hard drive with degraded sectors takes 7-10 days because we work slowly to avoid further damage. Very large drives (4TB+) take longer simply due to data volume.
+
+We don't charge rush fees, but we're honest about what's realistic. If you need data back in 24 hours, that's not always possible with mechanical drives, and we'll tell you that upfront.
+
