+The MacBook Pro M1 changed the game when Apple released it in late 2020. The unified architecture, the speed, the battery life, it felt genuinely revolutionary. But we have seen a growing number of M1 and M2 MacBook Pro units arrive at our Hyde Park workshop with one specific problem: GPU faults that render the machine either unusable or severely performance-degraded.
