+- **Don't force a restart**. If it won't turn on, holding the power button for 30 seconds occasionally helps, but don't repeatedly force it.
+- **Stop trying to charge it** if you suspect liquid damage. Let it dry. Continued charging can cause short circuits.
+- **Bring proof of purchase** if the machine is under Apple's warranty. We can often repair it free or at reduced cost.
+- **Write down the last thing you remember** before it stopped. ("I closed the lid and it wouldn't wake" is more useful than "it just died").
+
+[Book online at zasupport.com/book](https://zasupport.com/book) to secure your assessment slot, or [WhatsApp us on 064 529 5863](https://wa.me/27645295863) if you'd prefer to chat first about your specific situation. We're open Monday to Saturday in Hyde Park, and we handle both Intel and Apple Silicon Macs.
